    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-01-30T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-01-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="990"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d990">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60i12A/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister at Riga</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="13" xml:id="d990fn13">The position of the Department as set
                        forth in this telegram was communicated to the Estonian Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs in a note from the American Minister, dated March 27, 1929; not
                        printed (711.60i12A/16).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-30T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 30, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Your despatch No. 5805 and enclosed note regarding arbitration treaty.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>This Government is entirely willing to construe article I so as not to
                        require that cases be referred to the Hague Permanent Court of Arbitration
                        as long as Estonia does not become a party to the convention by which that
                        Court is established.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The Department does not understand that the Estonian Government asks that
                        the text of the article be changed.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
